main event: A UFO sighting was reported on 17 September 1955 in Bellingham, Washington, characterized by a round, white to red object with no sound or trail observed for a total of one hour.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by a tactical officer who observed it under radar conditions., The object was described as having a round shape and changing colors., The report indicated that the observation lacked sound or trail., Conclusion options included weather phenomena, possibly a balloon or aircraft, with insufficient data for definitive evaluation., The time of the observation aligned with an air drop in the area, suggesting potential connections with military activities.
witness description: Tactical officer, possibly associated with military intelligence
